NARRATIVE:

 

On January 12, 2023, at approximately 0630 hours, I, Tfc. Elmore was operating patrol vehicle, I-54, in Caroline County, Maryland. On that date and time, I responded to 704 Central avenue, Ridgely, Maryland 21660, to investigate a malicious destruction of property and domestic abuse complainant. Upon arriving at the residence, a white single-family house, I met with the complainant, Katie Lynn Horney, who was accompanied by her daughter, Aireyana Wilson. Katie advised she resides at the property with her children, 15-year-old Aireyana Wilson, 6-year-old Amiyah Horney, and twin 2-year-olds Makenna and Ma'Kayla Floyd. Katie advised on January 11, 2023, she petitioned a Temporary Protective Order(TPO) against Mardae Oneil Floyd, whom she identified as her ex-boyfriend and father of her twin daughters. The District Court of Maryland for Caroline county issued the TPO with an effective date through January 18, 2023, which is the date set for a Final Protective Order Hearing at the District Court of Maryland for Caroline County; District Court case number D-036-FM-23-807575. Katie advised she had to pretend she was going to work to get to the District Court in fear that Mardae would retaliate. Katie advised she was prompted to get a TPO after ongoing physical and mental abuse, including being strangled by Mardae on or about November 15, 2022, to the point she urinated on herself; Katie advised she did not report the alleged assault to law enforcement at that time. 

After getting the TPO, Katie advised that she notified Mardae of the TPO, and he responded that he didn't fear the police, going to jail, or a protective order; Katie advised Mardae stated he knew the TPO could not affect him since he was not served, Implicating that he was going to avoid being served  the TPO by law enforcement. Katie advised she retreated from 704 Central Avenue and fled to her grandmothers' residence to avoid further conflict with Mardae; Katie's' Grandmother, Patricia "Patty" Blunt, resides at 474 Dutchmans lane, Greensboro, Maryland 2139. Katie advised that Mardae had blocked her vehicle in the driveway at 704 Central Avenue with his vehicle, and she had to drive through her neighbor's property(702 Central Avenue) to leave the house. Tire tracks from Katie's driveway leading through her neighbor's front yard are imprinted in the soft soil. Katie advised on the night of January 11, 2023, someone knocked on her grandmother's door, and when they opened the door, no one was there. Katie suspected it to be Mardae based on his abusive behavior. I spoke with Patricia regarding the anonymous door knocks via telephone; Patrica advised that the incident occurred at approximately 11 pm on January 11, 2023. After the startling door knock, Katie advised that Mardae may go to the 704 Central avenue residence and destroy the property as he has done so in the past. Katie displayed a video on her cellphone she recorded on August 1, 2022, at approximately 6 pm; The video displayed several broken appliances and furniture, including interior doors, the front entry door, the master bedroom toilet, a vacuum cleaner, living room window, dishwasher, refrigerator, wooden chairs, and cabinets; the destruction left behind several pieces of broken glass, plastic, wood, porcelain and varies children toys, household products, and papers scattered across the floors. The damage appeared to exceed $2,500 doubtlessly. Katie advised she had fixed up the residence since then and arrived at 702 Central Avenue at approximately 6 am on January 12, 2023, to another incident of the residence being destroyed to the point that the conditions were unbearable.  

 

The interior of the 704 Central Avenue residence consists of one master bedroom with an adjoining master bathroom, one living room, one Kitchen with an adjoining side entrance hall, one hallway, three secondary bedrooms, and one secondary bathroom. 

 

In the living room, I observed the front entry door frame split(as if the door was forced open while locked), a destroyed ceiling fan(all four blades broken off, lying on the ground), a broken wooden dresser, a light fixture on the ground, holes in the drywall, and children toys scattered on the ground among the debris.

In the master bedroom, I observed the interior door separated from the door frame with two strips of wood still attached, damaged drywall, a broken vacuum cleaner, a broken jewelry box, a broken fan, a broken wooden dresser, a ripped bed, and sheets, ripped photographs of Katie and Aireyanna, and a heater with the cut cord.

In the master bathroom, I observed the interior door to be damaged and damaged drywall

in the Kitchen, I observed the refrigerator's cord to be cut, the oven's cord to be cut, broken wooden chairs, broken counter tops, a broken chandelier still attached to the ceiling, a broken table, damaged drywall, The kitchen window was covered by plastic from being busted out on August 1, 2022.

In the side entrance hall, The glass washer window was shattered, The dryer's door was broken off, and both appliance cords were cut from the wall outlets.

In the main hallway, I observed a heater appliance lying on the ground with a cut cord and a damaged flat-screen television.

In the secondary bathroom, I observed the entry door to be damaged, the drywall damaged, and a plastic crate with miscellaneous supplies turned over on the floor.

In Aireyana's bedroom, I observed a broken wooden dresser, a broken flat-screen television, a broken ceiling fan with its blades on the floor, damaged drywall, a broken air conditioning unit, and several pieces of teen girl clothes thrown among the debris.

Amiyah's bedroom didn't appear ransacked, as it lacked furniture.

In Makenna and Ma'Kayla's bedroom, I observed the entry door to be damaged, a heater with a cut cord, a turned-over baby crib, and a turned-over dresser.

 

Katies black Nissan Altima bearing Maryland registration "5EY8311" also displayed a damaged rear tail light and headlight. Katie advised Mardae damaged the vehicle on about October 1, 2022. The estimated cost of the damage is about $1,000. 

 

The interior floor of the residence was scattered with broken glass, wood, plastics, and various household products, including electronic accessories, toys, clothes, and household supplies. The estimated cost of damages doubtlessly exceeds $10,000. Katie advised Mardae has made statements in the past such as he would make them feel like they were living in a concentration camp. 

Based on my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper, including investigating prior domestic violence cases and my observations at 704 central avenue, including Katie's statements, the interior conditions of the residence, and verbal statements from neighbors, I know that Mardae attempted to mentally abuse Katie and her four children by using subtle tactics such as destroying their property, including items of necessity such as heating appliances, a washer and dryer, a refrigerator, a children's crib, televisions, family photographs, a vehicle, and toys. I know that Mardae attempted to impair their emotional development and sense of self-worth. Due to Mardae's pattern of behavior, Aireyana has missed school days, Katie has missed work and removed herself and her children from their home several times. Katie advised Mardae was released from a rehabilitation center in November 2022 after a brief treatment for drug and alcohol abuse. Katie believed Mardae to be under the influence of alcohol at the time he destroyed the residence; I observed a bottle cap that emanated the odor of an alcoholic beverage on the hallway floor. I, Tfc.Elmore submitted an application of charges against Mardae. As a mandated reporter I also provided the above stated observations to the Department of Human Services; On January 15th,2022, I contacted Child Protective Services agent Robin Bigalou and notified her of the case.

Upon review of the application for charges, District Court Commissioner, Lynda Blades determined there is not sufficient probable cause to issue charges against Mardae Floyd. All events occurred in Caroline County, Maryland.
